<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,577,711]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">
The mainly Oriental genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lower" authorityYear="1901" box="[456,571,577,603]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Polylopha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[456,571,577,603]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">Polylopha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes nine species, including the present new species and one new combination proposed herein. Diagnostic characters for the genus involve a large and strongly sclerotized signum (variously shaped) in the female genitalia, which differs from the signum of long bundled spines in the related genus 
<taxonomicName authority="(Diaknoff 1974)" baseAuthorityName="Diaknoff" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[151,465,685,711]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Lopharcha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
